--- body ---
## Context

PR 691 had `no checks reported`. /verify said nothing about it —
treating the PR body as narrative rather than running its own minimal
pre-gate checks.

The two other gaps from the original memos (pre-existing-failure
separation, body-claim audit) were removed from this ticket: the first
is per-project and moved to climate-finance 0079; the second was
dropped as the fragility of prose pattern-matching outweighs the
benefit over a convention.

## Actions

1. Setup phase of `/verify`: query `gh pr checks <pr>`. If empty, post
   a `verify: CI gap` informational comment. Not a bounce — just
   visible. Treat "pending" as not-yet-empty (no comment).

## Test

On a PR whose repo has no CI configured, expect a single
`verify: CI gap` comment on the gate's first pass. On a PR with CI
still pending, expect no such comment.

## Exit criteria

- CI absence produces a visible `verify: CI gap` note.
- No false positive when checks are merely pending.
- Memo-1 "ticket E (CI gap)" addressed.
